    <subsheetid>35a57eaa-1c2c-4e9a-9e5e-10fbbf458bbc</subsheetid>
    <display x="-30" y="60"/>
    <inputs>
      <input type="collection" name="Collection" narrative="Required : The collection to search" expr="[ApplicatioModel List]"/>
      <input type="text" name="Column Name" narrative="Required : The name of the column to search" expr="&amp;quot;Item Text&amp;quot;"/>
      <input type="text" name="Exact Value" narrative="Optional : The exact value to search for - this is case insensitive" expr="[Exec and View VBOName]"/>
      <input type="text" name="Regex" narrative="Optional : The regular expression to search for - this is case sensitive unless specified otherwise in the regular expression using &amp;quot;(?i)&amp;quot;" expr=""/>
    </inputs>
    <outputs>
      <output type="flag" name="Contains Search Term" narrative="Flag indicating if the collection found the given search term or not" stage="Contains Search Term 1"/>

      <input type="text" name="Tag Filter" narrative="Optionally, a tag mask to filter by. For example, &amp;quot;Account: Joint; -Balance: Overdrawn; Card: *Visa*&amp;quot; will include any items which match all the terms, ie. every item must have an 'Account: Joint' tag applied, no item can have a 'Balance: Overdrawn' tag applied, every item must have a tag applied which starts with 'Card: ' and then contains the text 'Visa'." expr=""/>

  <stage stageid="8f3e196b-2734-4832-95e0-0d040dccea6b" name="Note2" type="Note">
    <narrative>Code Coop is a useful menu test, because it tests Application Manager's ability to force the application to create its menus.

Code Coop builds its menus both lazily and dynamically (on the  fly), according to the current context.

Thus after the first launch, there are no menu items to perform a test match on; Application Manager has to instruct the application to build its menus first.</narrative>
    <displayx>-180</displayx>
    <displayy>90</displayy>
    <displaywidth>210</displaywidth>
    <displayheight>240</displayheight>
    <font family="Tahoma" size="10" style="Regular" color="000000"/>
  </stage>
</process>

        <field name="Batch" type="text" value="insert into company (name)&amp;#xD;&amp;#xA; select 'Acme, Inc.' union all&amp;#xD;&amp;#xA; select 'Bloggs Biscuits' union all&amp;#xD;&amp;#xA; select 'Carmichael and sons' union all&amp;#xD;&amp;#xA; select 'Delight'&amp;#xD;&amp;#xA;&amp;#xD;&amp;#xA;declare @acme int, @bloggs int, @carmichael int, @delight int;&amp;#xD;&amp;#xA;set @acme = (select id from company where name = 'Acme, Inc.')&amp;#xD;&amp;#xA;set @bloggs = (select id from company where name = 'Bloggs Biscuits')&amp;#xD;&amp;#xA;set @carmichael = (select id from company where name = 'Carmichael and sons')&amp;#xD;&amp;#xA;set @delight = (select id from company where name = 'Delight')&amp;#xD;&amp;#xA;&amp;#xD;&amp;#xA;select @acme, @bloggs, @carmichael, @delight&amp;#xD;&amp;#xA;&amp;#xD;&amp;#xA;-- Check for any nulls&amp;#xD;&amp;#xA;if (@acme + @bloggs + @carmichael + @delight) is null&amp;#xD;&amp;#xA;begin&amp;#xD;&amp;#xA;    raiserror('Invalid company found', 10, 1)&amp;#xD;&amp;#xA;    return&amp;#xD;&amp;#xA;end&amp;#xD;&amp;#xA;&amp;#xD;&amp;#xA;insert into client (name, dob, company)&amp;#xD;&amp;#xA;  select 'Andrew Atkinson', '19741214', @acme union all&amp;#xD;&amp;#xA;  select 'Bill Bloggs', '19590317', @bloggs union all&amp;#xD;&amp;#xA;  select 'Barry Bloggs', '19610828', @bloggs union all&amp;#xD;&amp;#xA;  select 'Carl Carmichael', null, @carmichael union all&amp;#xD;&amp;#xA;  select 'Chris Carmichael', '19820106', @carmichael union all&amp;#xD;&amp;#xA;  select 'Carrie Carmichael', '19830416', @carmichael union all&amp;#xD;&amp;#xA;  select 'Doris Deloitte', null, @delight&amp;#xD;&amp;#xA;&amp;#xD;&amp;#xA;-- Again, with the checking&amp;#xD;&amp;#xA;declare @andrew int, @bill int, @barry int, @carl int, @chris int, @carrie int, @doris int;&amp;#xD;&amp;#xA;set @andrew = (select id from client where name = 'Andrew Atkinson')&amp;#xD;&amp;#xA;set @bill = (select id from client where name = 'Bill Bloggs')&amp;#xD;&amp;#xA;set @barry = (select id from client where name = 'Barry Bloggs')&amp;#xD;&amp;#xA;set @carl = (select id from client where name = 'Carl Carmichael')&amp;#xD;&amp;#xA;set @chris = (select id from client where name = 'Chris Carmichael')&amp;#xD;&amp;#xA;set @carrie = (select id from client where name = 'Carrie Carmichael')&amp;#xD;&amp;#xA;set @doris = (select id from client where name = 'Doris Deloitte')&amp;#xD;&amp;#xA;&amp;#xD;&amp;#xA;if (@andrew + @bill + @barry + @carl + @chris + @carrie + @doris) is null&amp;#xD;&amp;#xA;begin&amp;#xD;&amp;#xA;    raiserror('Invalid client found', 10, 1)&amp;#xD;&amp;#xA;    return&amp;#xD;&amp;#xA;end&amp;#xD;&amp;#xA;&amp;#xD;&amp;#xA;declare @pending int, @dispatched int, @delivered int, @paid int&amp;#xD;&amp;#xA;set @pending = 1&amp;#xD;&amp;#xA;set @dispatched = 2&amp;#xD;&amp;#xA;set @delivered = 3&amp;#xD;&amp;#xA;set @paid = 4&amp;#xD;&amp;#xA;&amp;#xD;&amp;#xA;declare @invoiceid int&amp;#xD;&amp;#xA;&amp;#xD;&amp;#xA;-- Invoice 1 &amp;amp; 2: A simple fisherman&amp;#xD;&amp;#xA;insert into invoice (company, client, date, state)&amp;#xD;&amp;#xA;  select @acme, @andrew, '20130612', @pending&amp;#xD;&amp;#xA;set @invoiceid = scope_identity()&amp;#xD;&amp;#xA;insert into invoiceentry (section, subsection, name, invoice, price) values ('Fishing', 'Rods', 'Budget-o-rod', @invoiceid, 1000)&amp;#xD;&amp;#xA;&amp;#xD;&amp;#xA;insert into invoice (company, client, date, state)&amp;#xD;&amp;#xA;
